    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Los Angeles, on a Bike</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>T J Mitchell letter holds transit problems in Los Angeles could be eased by making city a safer place to get around on a bike</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In your Sept. 19 news article about the transit strike in Los Angeles, you do not mention the most efficient and reliable commuter vehicle in use in this city: the bicycle. If Mayor Richard J. Riordan had spent some of his tenure improving bicycle facilities, he might have been spared the spectacle of people on street corners begging drivers to pick them up.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In your Sept. 19 news article about the transit strike in Los Angeles, you do not mention the most efficient and reliable commuter vehicle in use in this city: the bicycle. If Mayor Richard J. Riordan had spent some of his tenure improving bicycle facilities, he might have been spared the spectacle of people on street corners begging drivers to pick them up.</p>
        <p>Make Los Angeles a safer place to get around on a bike, and swarms of health-conscious Angelenos will ride to work, easing the strain on the clogged freeways and overcrowded public transportation systems.</p>
        <p>T. J. MITCHELL  Los Angeles, Sept. 19, 2000</p>
      </block>
